 This document provides a step-by-step guide to publishing a standalone story from a dataset using various technologies. It includes instructions on setting up the necessary tools and frameworks, creating a Git repository, and building a simple web page using a template. The resulting page will serve as a starting point for further development in the subsequent chapters.

Summary:

1. Set up the necessary tools and frameworks, including Node.js, npm, Yeoman, Yeogurt generator, Gulp, and BrowserSync.
2. Create a new project using the Yeogurt generator and respond to the prompt to configure the project name, HTML preprocessor, JavaScript preprocessor, style preprocessor, and Sass syntax.
3. Test the default homepage by running the test server and visiting localhost:3000 in the browser.
4. Navigate to the project directory and commit the work to Git.

Keywords: Node.js, npm, Yeoman, Yeogurt generator, Gulp, BrowserSync, Git, web page, template.

